{
  "texts": [
    "Several researchers have attempted to develop thresholds for standard behavioral indicators (e.g., frequency of gambling, amount spent) that differentiate lower-from higher-risk gambling to form lower risk gambling limits (Hodgins et al., 2023; Louderback et al., 2021) -these, or similar thresholdstyle indicators, could plausibly serve as targets, either individually or in combination.",
    "Overall, the variation and lack of a standard approach to classification presents a challenge to constructing and comparing ML models, as there is no agreed-upon specification to label training data appropriately.",
    "Given the diversity of outcome variables and definitions of risk, we do not propose a single ground truth.",
    "Instead, we recommend a suite of benchmarks that can evolve over time as the domain continues to develop and as a clearer definition of \"at-risk\" emerges.",
    "We do, however, advocate for transparency in how at-risk status is determined to ensure the process can be replicated in real-world environments."
  ]
}